“Don’t” You reduce to ashes all asuras
by mere sight?

44:31.250 --> 44:32.250
But You direct Your weapons against them so
that even the inimical ones, purified by the

44:32.250 --> 44:33.250
missiles, may attain the higher worlds.

44:33.250 --> 44:34.250
Such is Your most kindly intention towards
them.

44:34.250 --> 44:35.250
“If the eyes of the asuras had not been
put out by the terrible flashes of the mass

44:35.250 --> 44:36.250
of light issuing from Your sword or by the
copious lustre of Your spearpoint, it is because

44:36.250 --> 44:37.250
they saw also Your face resembling the moon,
giving out (cool) rays.

44:37.250 --> 44:38.250
“O Devi, Your nature is to subdue the conduct
of the wicked; this Your peerless beauty is

44:38.250 --> 44:39.250
inconceivable for others; Your power destroys
those who have robbed the Devas of their prowess,

44:39.250 --> 44:40.250
and You have thus manifested Your compassion
even towards the enemies.

44:40.250 --> 44:41.250
“What is Your prowess to be compared to?

44:41.250 --> 44:42.250
Where can one find this beauty (of Yours)
most charming, (yet) striking fear in enemies?

44:42.250 --> 44:43.250
Compassion in heart and relentlessness in
battle are seen, O Devi, O Bestower of boons,

44:43.250 --> 44:44.250
only in You in all the three worlds!

44:44.250 --> 44:45.250
“Through the destruction of the enemies
all these three worlds have been saved by

44:45.250 --> 44:46.250
You.

44:46.250 --> 44:47.250
Having killed them in the battle-front, You
have led even those hosts of enemies to heaven,

44:47.250 --> 44:48.250
and You have dispelled our fear of the frenzied
enemies of the Devas.

44:48.250 --> 44:49.250
Salutation to You!

44:49.250 --> 44:50.250
“O Devi, protect us with Your spear.

44:50.250 --> 44:51.250
O Ambika, protect us with Your sword, protect
us by the sound of Your bell and by the twang

44:51.250 --> 44:52.250
of Your bow-string.

44:52.250 --> 44:53.250
“O Candika, guard us in the east, in the
west, in the north and in the south by the

44:53.250 --> 44:54.250
brandishing of Your spear.

44:54.250 --> 44:55.250
O Iswari!

44:55.250 --> 44:56.250
“Protect us and the earth with those lovely
forms of Yours moving about in the three worlds,

44:56.250 --> 44:57.250
as also with Your exceedingly terrible forms.

44:57.250 --> 44:58.250
“O Ambika, protect us on every side with
Your sword, spear and club and whatever other

44:58.250 --> 44:58.257
weapons Your sprite-like (soft) hand has touched."
